## Data Model

### Identifier strategy

Every primary entity has two identifiers:
- `id` INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT — internal, dense for joins
- `ulid` TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE — external, used in URLs and APIs

Why both: integer IDs are efficient for joins and indexing; ULIDs are stable, time-sortable, URL-safe, and don't leak count information externally. URLs always use ULIDs (`/partners/01HXY...`); internal joins use integer IDs.

### Soft delete

`firms` and `partners` have `deleted_at TIMESTAMP NULL`. Default queries exclude soft-deleted rows. The `audit_ledger` and `import_markdown` operations can opt to include them via flag.

`contact_log`, `notes`, and `audit_log` are append-only — no soft delete.

