### Triggers

```sql
CREATE TRIGGER firms_updated_at AFTER UPDATE ON firms
BEGIN
  UPDATE firms SET updated_at = CURRENT_TIMESTAMP WHERE id = NEW.id;
END;

CREATE TRIGGER partners_updated_at AFTER UPDATE ON partners
BEGIN
  UPDATE partners SET updated_at = CURRENT_TIMESTAMP WHERE id = NEW.id;
END;
```

Note: audit-log entries are written in the **service layer**, not via DB triggers. This is deliberate — services have the actor and transport context that DB triggers cannot easily access.

### Indexes

```sql
CREATE INDEX idx_firms_tier ON firms(tier) WHERE deleted_at IS NULL;
CREATE INDEX idx_firms_state ON firms(relationship_state) WHERE deleted_at IS NULL;
CREATE INDEX idx_partners_firm ON partners(firm_id) WHERE deleted_at IS NULL;
CREATE INDEX idx_partners_next_touch ON partners(next_planned_touch_date) WHERE deleted_at IS NULL;
CREATE INDEX idx_partners_last_contact ON partners(last_contact_date) WHERE deleted_at IS NULL;
CREATE INDEX idx_contact_log_partner ON contact_log(partner_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_contact_log_date ON contact_log(contact_date);
CREATE INDEX idx_notes_entity ON notes(entity_type, entity_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_audit_entity ON audit_log(entity_type, entity_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_audit_timestamp ON audit_log(timestamp);
```

### Full-text search

SQLite FTS5 virtual tables for search across firm names, partner names, notes bodies, and contact summaries. Updated via triggers on the underlying tables.

```sql
CREATE VIRTUAL TABLE search_index USING fts5(
  entity_type, entity_ulid, primary_text, secondary_text,
  tokenize='unicode61 remove_diacritics 2'
);
```

Service layer keeps `search_index` in sync on every mutation.

