[FF logo]   Dashboard  Firms  Plan  Audit  Notes        [⌕ search]   [logout]
```

Logo: "FF" monogram in Crimson Pro Bold Slate Blue, with Vermillion 3px underline (per milanese-visual logo spec). Clicking goes to dashboard.

### Dashboard

Three-column on desktop, single-column on mobile. Cards:

1. **Pipeline overview** — 5 primary firms as cards in a row. Each shows firm name, current state pill, sparkline of last-12-months contact frequency, and a "view" link. Below: collapsible specialist tier.
2. **Upcoming touches** — Next 14 days. List rows with partner name, firm, days until/overdue, planned topic. Overdue rows have Vermillion left-border accent.
3. **Audit highlights** — Top 3 actions from the latest audit_ledger run. Each with a "do this" CTA leading to the relevant partner page.

Empty-state messaging is dignified — no jokes, no exclamation marks. Example: "No contacts logged in the last 30 days. Plan your next outreach." with a Plan-Quarter button.

### Firm Detail Page

Header (Slate Blue): firm name (Crimson Pro 36px), tier badge, region, current state pill.
Below header (white card): firm-level notes, edit-in-place.
Partner section: cards in a grid, each showing partner name, practice, last contact, status pill. Click for partner page.
Contact timeline section (full-width below partners): chronological list of all contacts across all partners at this firm, with channel icons.

### Partner Detail Page

Header: partner name (Crimson Pro 36px), firm + practice, status pill, "Log contact" primary button (Vermillion).
Body grid (2 columns desktop, 1 column mobile):
- Left: partner facts panel (seniority, location, introduced-via, first contact, last contact, next planned touch, next planned topic — all inline-editable).
- Right: follow-ups outstanding list with check-off buttons.
Full-width below: contact timeline (vertical), most recent first. Each contact entry expands to show full value-given/value-received/summary/follow-up.
Bottom: notes section (chronological list, "Add note" button).

### Plan Page

Year selector (default: current year).
Four-card grid for Q1–Q4. Current quarter card is expanded:
- Topic field (editable inline).
- Suggested contacts list (from `plan_quarter` API).
- Each row has a "Log contact" inline button.

### Audit Page

Calls `GET /api/v1/audit/report` on load.
Sections rendered as cards: Coverage Gaps, Dormant Relationships, Open Follow-Ups, Reciprocity Imbalances, Summary Actions.
Summary Actions presented as a numbered checklist with strikethrough on completion (state stored client-side only — these are recommendations, not tasks).

### Audit Log Page (`/audit/log`)

Power-user view. Filterable list of every mutation. Each row clickable to expand into a before/after diff (JSON, syntax highlighted).
Default view: last 50 entries, newest first.
Filters: entity type, entity ULID, date range, action type.

### Search Page

Single input at top. Results grouped by entity type (firms, partners, notes, contacts). Each result shows snippet with highlighted match. Click navigates to the entity page.

### Settings Page

Three sections:
1. **API token** — view masked token, "rotate" button (generates new token, displays once, instructs to update Claude MCP config and any other clients).
2. **Backup status** — last backup timestamp, last backup size, "trigger now" button.
3. **System** — schema version, container build hash, dependency versions. Plain text for diagnostics.

### Empty / Loading / Error states

Every page handles three states. Components use a `<Skeleton />` placeholder during fetch, an `<EmptyState />` when no data, and an `<ErrorBoundary />` for fetch failures with a "retry" button and the error code.

